Changelog: [s390] dump on panic support

BZ 228050 & 227841

Re-IPL (reboot) with alternate paramters and dump on panic.

With the new feature it is possible to specify a new ccw or fcp
re-IPL device under Linux. When the user calls reboot, the system
automacially IPLs from the specified
device.

In addition to that, it is possible to specify a ccw or fcp dump
device which is IPL-ed in case of a kernel panic.


Summary:     Kernel new function: Reipl with alternate paramters and dump on
             panic.
Description: With the new feature it is possible to specify a new ccw or fcp
